WEBVTT

00:05.306 --> 00:06.608
* Ah, look at me get down *

00:06.674 --> 00:07.842
* Whoo, check him out *

00:07.909 --> 00:09.143
* Boy, I'm steppin' *

00:09.210 --> 00:10.945
* All right *

00:11.012 --> 00:12.246
* What you talkin' about? *

00:12.313 --> 00:13.581
* Yeeoww *

00:21.656 --> 00:23.090
That's me...

00:23.157 --> 00:25.026
Hugh Hefner.

00:26.761 --> 00:28.763
* Are you ready *

00:28.830 --> 00:32.099
I took a personal
investment of $600...

00:32.166 --> 00:34.536
and turned it
into a global empire.

00:36.103 --> 00:38.172
* Are you ready *

00:38.239 --> 00:40.542
You may
think you know me...

00:40.608 --> 00:42.777
the guy who has it all.

00:42.844 --> 00:44.345
Would you welcome
Hugh Hefner.

00:46.380 --> 00:47.649
* Get on down *

00:47.715 --> 00:48.883
The lavish mansion.

00:48.950 --> 00:50.184
* Look at me get down *

00:50.251 --> 00:51.853
* Whoo, check him out *

00:53.821 --> 00:57.024
The legendary parties.

00:57.091 --> 00:59.260
He would invite all
these beautiful girls.

00:59.326 --> 01:02.029
I mean, you talk about, like,
dying and going to heaven.

01:02.096 --> 01:04.031
It was amazing.

01:06.267 --> 01:08.903
And, of course, the women.

01:10.472 --> 01:12.239
Can you estimate

01:12.306 --> 01:14.842
just how many ladies
you have known?

01:14.909 --> 01:16.478
No, I can't.

01:16.544 --> 01:17.879
* Yeeoww *

01:17.945 --> 01:19.447
And what started it all...

01:19.514 --> 01:21.683
Playboy magazine.

01:23.250 --> 01:25.853
But for everything
you've heard about me,

01:25.920 --> 01:29.557
there's probably a lot
you don't know.

01:29.624 --> 01:31.358
For all the people
who loved me,

01:31.425 --> 01:34.729
there were plenty
who wanted to take me down.

01:34.796 --> 01:38.099
Playboy openly
advocates the overthrow

01:38.165 --> 01:40.768
of Judeo Christian
standards.

01:40.835 --> 01:44.305
There were times
when I felt worn down,

01:44.371 --> 01:45.973
trying to escape.

01:46.040 --> 01:48.175
You know, you pick yourself up
and you fight it again.

01:48.242 --> 01:53.147
I've been investigated
by the FBI and the DEA.

01:53.214 --> 01:55.082
Hefner said that
prosecutors kept pressuring

01:55.149 --> 01:58.252
Miss Arnstein to testify
against her boss in drug cases.

01:58.319 --> 02:01.255
Attacked by the media
and religious groups.

02:01.322 --> 02:03.157
Well, with this I think
that you'll agree,

02:03.224 --> 02:04.592
it's a sniggering
kind of sex.

02:04.659 --> 02:06.928
It certainly isn't
a healthy approach to sex.

02:06.994 --> 02:09.597
And pushed
to the brink of bankruptcy.

02:09.664 --> 02:13.367
Hef, you are
killing yourself.

02:13.434 --> 02:17.404
But my magazine
wasn't just about naked women.

02:17.471 --> 02:19.373
It was breaking down barriers,

02:19.440 --> 02:23.044
starting a cultural
conversation about sexuality,

02:23.110 --> 02:26.247
and standing up
for social justice.

02:26.313 --> 02:29.016
Hugh Hefner
identified unequivocally

02:29.083 --> 02:30.818
with the civil rights movement
of that time.

02:30.885 --> 02:35.222
Giving a platform to Dr. King,
a platform to Malcolm X.

02:35.289 --> 02:37.324
By any means
necessary.

02:37.391 --> 02:40.494
I've been
called a pornographer...

02:40.562 --> 02:42.029
a smut peddler...

02:42.096 --> 02:43.197
and a sexist.

02:43.264 --> 02:45.232
The day that you are
willing to come out here

02:45.299 --> 02:48.035
with a cottontail attached
to your rear end...

02:50.705 --> 02:53.675
And my lifestyle
hasn't always been easy

02:53.741 --> 02:55.610
on the people closest to me.

02:55.677 --> 02:59.180
He dates other girls,
and... I don't like it.

02:59.246 --> 03:00.548
And he knows
I don't like it.

03:01.883 --> 03:03.651
I've gained enemies...

03:03.718 --> 03:05.486
and lost friends.

03:05.553 --> 03:08.489
An already
emotionally troubled woman

03:08.556 --> 03:11.559
was pushed
beyond endurance...

03:11.626 --> 03:13.695
and she killed herself.

03:16.163 --> 03:18.032
The conception of Playboy

03:18.099 --> 03:22.637
came from my dad's irritation
with the status quo.

03:22.704 --> 03:25.640
So, the entire magazine
came to be

03:25.707 --> 03:28.442
because of one guy
who was pretty upset

03:28.509 --> 03:32.313
with how most people
interpreted and defined sex.

03:34.148 --> 03:36.951
I've lived a life
most could only dream of.

03:41.555 --> 03:42.957
This is my story.

03:46.360 --> 03:49.063
Or at least
how I remember it.

03:50.698 --> 03:54.401
* Every little movement *

03:54.468 --> 03:58.773
* Every little thing
you do *

03:58.840 --> 04:01.242
* Is it sleight of hand *

04:01.308 --> 04:06.447
* That commands
my heart to love you *

04:06.513 --> 04:10.484
* Every little movement *

04:10.551 --> 04:14.121
* Every little movement **

04:34.108 --> 04:35.042
Hef?

04:35.109 --> 04:36.043
Oh! Bobbie.

04:36.110 --> 04:37.812
- Hef!
- What is it?

04:37.879 --> 04:39.947
The cops
are downstairs.

04:40.014 --> 04:42.383
Just tell them
I'll deal with it tomorrow.

04:42.449 --> 04:44.051
They're here for you.

04:45.887 --> 04:48.189
This morning a man
is on trial in Chicago,

04:48.255 --> 04:51.292
charged with violating that
city's laws against obscenity.

04:53.594 --> 04:57.531
He's Hugh Hefner, publisher
of Playboy magazine.

04:57.598 --> 04:59.767
The issue has been the cause
of many court cases

04:59.834 --> 05:02.169
involving motion pictures,
books, and magazines,

05:02.236 --> 05:04.638
and various
court decisions have left

05:04.706 --> 05:06.140
considerable gray areas

05:06.207 --> 05:08.710
in determining just what
is salacious and obscene.

05:11.612 --> 05:16.984
Men who would
stand by and see their women

05:17.051 --> 05:20.121
degraded and debased,
as they are with the breast

05:20.187 --> 05:23.357
and the buttock
presentation by Playboy,

05:23.424 --> 05:26.160
are not men at all.

05:26.227 --> 05:28.362
What you're
accusing me of, in essence,

05:28.429 --> 05:30.264
is taking things
that previously were taboo

05:30.331 --> 05:32.599
and considered obscene
and objectionable

05:32.666 --> 05:34.969
and making them tasteful
and acceptable.

05:35.036 --> 05:36.637
Tonight,
the first of three

05:36.704 --> 05:38.239
special reports
on the controversy.

05:38.305 --> 05:40.307
The only thing
wrong with sex is the fact

05:40.374 --> 05:43.310
that we have a great tendency
to treat it as something

05:43.377 --> 05:46.447
shameful and guilty
and taboo-ridden,

05:46.513 --> 05:47.782
and this is what causes

05:47.849 --> 05:49.350
the major problems,
not the sex itself.

05:57.324 --> 06:00.361
Mr. Hefner...

06:00.427 --> 06:02.730
why did you start Playboy?

06:04.698 --> 06:07.001
Well...

06:07.068 --> 06:08.702
that's
a tough question.

06:08.770 --> 06:10.671
Just take your time.

06:14.241 --> 06:18.579
* I'll never smile again *

06:18.645 --> 06:21.615
Long before
the mansions, before the clubs,

06:21.682 --> 06:25.753
the parties, before the women,
before the magazine...

06:25.820 --> 06:27.755
there was just me.

06:27.822 --> 06:30.257
Hugh Marston Hefner.

06:30.324 --> 06:33.494
I was born
in Chicago in 1926.

06:33.560 --> 06:37.464
My parents were hardworking
Midwestern protestants

06:37.531 --> 06:38.933
who didn't allow dancing,

06:39.000 --> 06:42.203
drinking, or swearing
in the house.

06:42.269 --> 06:45.506
My father spent most
of his time at the office...

06:45.572 --> 06:48.509
and my mother was
emotionally distant toward me

06:48.575 --> 06:51.078
and my younger brother, Keith.

06:51.145 --> 06:53.414
I think that the major thing
that I missed,

06:53.480 --> 06:57.618
and that my parents missed
in their own childhood...

06:57.684 --> 07:01.655
because it's been passed from
generation to generation...

07:01.722 --> 07:03.958
was the inability
to show love

07:04.025 --> 07:07.328
in an emotional
and physical way.

07:07.394 --> 07:09.596
No hugging.

07:09.663 --> 07:11.398
No show
of any kind of emotion.

07:11.465 --> 07:15.569
With my home life
lacking the affection I craved,

07:15.636 --> 07:18.539
I escaped into
a world of fantasy.

07:20.507 --> 07:23.110
And for me,
that was cartooning.

07:25.146 --> 07:27.581
As a young man,
he was quite shy,

07:27.648 --> 07:32.119
and so he created his fantasy
life by writing stories

07:32.186 --> 07:33.888
and by cartooning his life...

07:35.256 --> 07:37.925
...where he could
live out the kind of life

07:37.992 --> 07:41.963
that he really wanted,
that he fantasized about.

07:42.029 --> 07:46.133
This was a way of compensating
for that shyness,

07:46.200 --> 07:49.470
and it has continued on
through his whole life.

07:49.536 --> 07:51.472
By the time I
reached high school,

07:51.538 --> 07:55.877
I'd even created an alter ego
named Goo Heffer...

07:55.943 --> 07:58.579
who was confident and popular.

08:00.381 --> 08:02.049
But when I wanted
to imagine a life

08:02.116 --> 08:05.052
far more exciting
than my own,

08:05.119 --> 08:08.289
there was only one place to go.

08:19.934 --> 08:21.502
When I was in my teens,

08:21.568 --> 08:25.172
I got a job at the local
movie theater.

08:25.239 --> 08:28.342
I was taken to movies
when I was very young,

08:28.409 --> 08:32.446
and from very early on,
up on that screen,

08:32.513 --> 08:36.350
were all the dreams
of the possibilities.

08:36.417 --> 08:38.019
You'd come out of that movie
and you'd feel like

08:38.085 --> 08:40.821
you were Bogart
or the leading man.

08:40.888 --> 08:43.357
The heroine loved you
in a very pure way,

08:43.424 --> 08:46.060
and I think that was what I
was really looking for.

08:47.828 --> 08:51.632
The heroine
I wanted in my life...

08:51.698 --> 08:55.069
was Betty Conklin.

08:55.136 --> 08:58.039
Everyone who's ever
been a teenager

08:58.105 --> 09:00.441
has known
a Betty Conklin.

09:01.943 --> 09:04.045
I was just
overwhelmed by her.

09:04.111 --> 09:06.080
There was a brief period
of time in which I thought

09:06.147 --> 09:10.084
it might really be, you know,
a romantic relationship.

09:10.151 --> 09:14.288
She picked my buddy
instead of me,

09:14.355 --> 09:18.659
and that told me more
than I wanted to know.

09:18.725 --> 09:22.629
And that was the period
when I reinvented myself.

09:25.532 --> 09:28.169
* Let your tear fall, baby *

09:28.235 --> 09:30.037
Over the next few years,

09:30.104 --> 09:32.239
I was determined
to transform myself

09:32.306 --> 09:34.875
into the leading man
I'd seen on screen.

09:34.942 --> 09:39.680
So I turned to my favorite
magazine for help... Esquire.

09:41.515 --> 09:44.685
Esquire was the first
men's magazine.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.853
It was the only magazine
that sort of went after

09:46.920 --> 09:48.322
the general interests of men.

09:48.389 --> 09:51.125
The reason there weren't
more magazines for men

09:51.192 --> 09:52.859
is because magazines,

09:52.926 --> 09:56.230
and to a slightly
lesser extent, reading,

09:56.297 --> 09:58.532
was seen as like a pursuit
that women did.

09:58.599 --> 10:01.535
And it was kinda revolutionary
to create a magazine for men

10:01.602 --> 10:03.070
and that it would
be successful,

10:03.137 --> 10:05.872
and it was successful
pretty rapidly.

10:05.939 --> 10:08.109
I had just
discovered Esquire

10:08.175 --> 10:09.676
for the very first time,

10:09.743 --> 10:12.513
and the world
suggested by Esquire.

10:12.579 --> 10:17.218
The cartoons, the fiction,
the fashion,

10:17.284 --> 10:20.754
and certainly the pin-ups,
which were called Petty Girls.

10:20.821 --> 10:24.225
The Petty Girls became
my first favorite pin-up.

10:24.291 --> 10:27.028
And I covered my walls with them
when I was first in high school.

10:27.094 --> 10:29.130
* Let your tear fall, baby *

10:29.196 --> 10:30.564
Esquire just opened my eyes

10:30.631 --> 10:33.800
to a whole other world
that was only hinted at

10:33.867 --> 10:37.404
in the movies of the time.

10:37.471 --> 10:41.708
Reading Esquire changed
my whole approach to life.

10:41.775 --> 10:45.279
I was more confident
and outgoing.

10:45.346 --> 10:51.052
* If you said good-bye **

10:52.719 --> 10:54.821
And,
by the end of high school,

10:54.888 --> 10:56.823
I met someone.

10:56.890 --> 10:59.326
Her name was Millie Williams.

10:59.393 --> 11:01.995
* I've got a girl
that lives up on a hill *

11:02.063 --> 11:04.831
I felt an instant
connection with Millie.

11:04.898 --> 11:07.101
She got my sense of humor,

11:07.168 --> 11:09.370
liked the way I dressed.

11:09.436 --> 11:11.672
But most importantly...

11:11.738 --> 11:13.740
she understood me.

11:13.807 --> 11:17.311
I met Hef at a graduation party,
the week of graduation.

11:17.378 --> 11:21.215
He made me feel very important
and that he liked me a lot.

11:21.282 --> 11:23.184
And he was fun to be with.

11:23.250 --> 11:25.018
I really think that Millie

11:25.086 --> 11:28.021
was the first girl
that he really loved,

11:28.089 --> 11:31.225
rather than just being
in love with from afar.

11:31.292 --> 11:34.628
That he really loved,
who loved him back.

11:34.695 --> 11:37.030
We started
getting serious,

11:37.098 --> 11:38.465
and when Millie
registered for college

11:38.532 --> 11:41.268
at the University
of Illinois...

11:41.335 --> 11:42.903
I decided to follow her.

11:42.969 --> 11:44.471
* Hey, man, I'm happy *

11:44.538 --> 11:47.641
* I am happy as a baby boy *

11:47.708 --> 11:50.511
But, like
most couples of the day,

11:50.577 --> 11:54.648
our private life
was pretty innocent.

11:54.715 --> 11:57.118
Everyone, I think,
had the same routine,

11:57.184 --> 11:59.520
in which sexually
you did many things,

11:59.586 --> 12:01.255
but you didn't
do the thing.

12:01.322 --> 12:04.358
And this was very typical,
and somehow that kept you,

12:04.425 --> 12:06.593
you know,
God wasn't frowning.

12:06.660 --> 12:08.229
* Little woman I'm through *

12:12.399 --> 12:15.202
My college life
was fairly typical

12:15.269 --> 12:17.904
for the first few semesters.

12:17.971 --> 12:20.407
But in my junior year,

12:20.474 --> 12:22.943
everything changed...

12:23.009 --> 12:26.813
when a groundbreaking
psychological study came out...

12:26.880 --> 12:28.249
that would open my eyes

12:28.315 --> 12:30.684
to a completely
different side of life.

12:35.656 --> 12:39.660
In 1948,
sexologist Alfred Kinsey

12:39.726 --> 12:44.465
published a massive study
of American male sexuality.

12:44.531 --> 12:49.503
In this study, he showed
that American men and women

12:49.570 --> 12:51.372
had a lot more
sexual experience

12:51.438 --> 12:53.407
than most people
were willing to admit to.

12:53.474 --> 12:57.411
Affairs, same-sex experiences,
multiple partners.

12:57.478 --> 13:00.847
And it made news
all across the country.

13:02.783 --> 13:04.518
You have to remember,

13:04.585 --> 13:08.422
back in the '40s, no one
was talking about sex.

13:08.489 --> 13:10.424
In Hollywood pictures,
a man and a woman

13:10.491 --> 13:13.026
weren't allowed to be
shown in bed together...

13:13.093 --> 13:14.561
not even married couples.

13:14.628 --> 13:16.863
That attitude was reflected

13:16.930 --> 13:19.200
in books
and other mass media.

13:19.266 --> 13:21.067
There was a kind of a...

13:21.134 --> 13:24.137
Norman Rockwell
view of the world

13:24.205 --> 13:26.307
that didn't exist,

13:26.373 --> 13:28.809
and it bothered me
very much.

13:30.977 --> 13:34.381
* I was standing
on the corner *

13:34.448 --> 13:36.149
* When I heard
my bulldog bark *

13:36.217 --> 13:39.052
Kinsey's expose
of the hypocrisy in our country

13:39.119 --> 13:41.722
was a revelation to me...

13:41.788 --> 13:46.260
and I was inspired to start
voicing my own opinion.

13:46.327 --> 13:48.262
We've got it down
to these six.

13:48.329 --> 13:51.298
I became editor of
the college humor magazine...

13:51.365 --> 13:52.666
called Shaft.

13:52.733 --> 13:53.834
This one.

13:53.900 --> 13:56.270
And, taking a lead
from Kinsey...

13:56.337 --> 13:59.340
I used it as a sounding board
for my own sexual beliefs.

13:59.406 --> 14:01.842
* Stagger Lee told Billy *

14:01.908 --> 14:03.644
Shaft magazine had an editorial

14:03.710 --> 14:08.081
about the Kinsey report
and about sexual repression

14:08.148 --> 14:10.751
and the hurt
and hypocrisy of it.

14:10.817 --> 14:14.020
I wrote a great deal
about the really moral issues.

14:14.087 --> 14:15.556
That what we call moral,

14:15.622 --> 14:17.391
in every other area
of human activity,

14:17.458 --> 14:19.159
is what is good
for people.

14:19.226 --> 14:21.962
And our traditional values
related to sex

14:22.028 --> 14:23.364
are not good for people.

14:23.430 --> 14:25.432
They hurt people.
They're hypocritical.

14:25.499 --> 14:26.867
* Go, Stagger Lee *

14:26.933 --> 14:30.003
I started
drawing racy cartoons,

14:30.070 --> 14:32.138
writing essays about sex,

14:32.205 --> 14:33.840
and challenging conformity.

14:33.907 --> 14:37.578
I think what my father taught me
about freedom of expression...

14:37.644 --> 14:41.315
is that it's okay to not be PC

14:41.382 --> 14:42.583
when you're having
a conversation

14:42.649 --> 14:44.451
about something
that really matters.

14:44.518 --> 14:47.521
It's okay to challenge
other people's beliefs

14:47.588 --> 14:48.989
and your own beliefs.

14:49.055 --> 14:51.292
I also
introduced a feature

14:51.358 --> 14:53.394
that was an instant hit
on campus.

14:53.460 --> 14:55.696
* Stagger Lee and Billy *

14:55.762 --> 14:58.699
When Hef was working
on Shaft magazine,

14:58.765 --> 15:01.201
he started Coed of the Month.

15:01.268 --> 15:02.903
And it would be a girl,

15:02.969 --> 15:05.071
and it would have
career information

15:05.138 --> 15:06.473
and her statistics

15:06.540 --> 15:08.609
and what she was into
and what she liked.

15:08.675 --> 15:13.246
So he already had
that idea pre- Playboy.

15:14.681 --> 15:15.882
I loved
the creative freedom

15:15.949 --> 15:19.052
that writing for Shaft
offered me.

15:19.119 --> 15:20.687
* Now, look out, Stagger, go *

15:20.754 --> 15:22.956
And the best part was

15:23.023 --> 15:26.760
I could use my cartoons to send
hidden messages to Millie.

15:29.463 --> 15:31.532
As he was talking
about these laws,

15:31.598 --> 15:34.200
these restrictive laws
and repressive things,

15:34.267 --> 15:36.937
it was very easy
to discuss this together

15:37.003 --> 15:39.540
and say how wrong this
all was, because we both,

15:39.606 --> 15:41.975
we felt the same way,
despite my Catholic background

15:42.042 --> 15:43.510
and his background.

15:43.577 --> 15:48.048
And um, we found we had
a lot of the same attitudes.

15:48.114 --> 15:50.517
Our shared views
brought us closer...

15:50.584 --> 15:54.220
both emotionally
and physically.

15:54.287 --> 15:59.460
My romance with Millie, then,
was an extended, uh, foreplay

15:59.526 --> 16:02.028
until she graduated
from college.

16:02.095 --> 16:05.799
We had sex for the first time
the summer of '48.

16:05.866 --> 16:07.300
I would've been 22.

16:12.072 --> 16:15.509
A few months
after graduation...

16:15.576 --> 16:19.546
I did what everyone else
did in those days.

16:19.613 --> 16:22.483
I proposed
to my college sweetheart.

16:28.389 --> 16:30.524
And we should be able
to trust one another.

16:30.591 --> 16:31.925
Don't smile it away...

16:31.992 --> 16:33.460
But then one night...

16:33.527 --> 16:35.362
Millie dropped a bombshell.

16:35.429 --> 16:36.997
You were in love with
a schoolgirl notion

16:37.063 --> 16:38.198
of a popular novelist!

16:38.264 --> 16:39.566
Millie.

16:42.903 --> 16:45.071
Millie!

16:45.138 --> 16:46.239
What was that about?

16:46.306 --> 16:48.341
I just want
to go home.

16:48.409 --> 16:49.810
Everything okay?

16:49.876 --> 16:51.378
That night...

16:51.445 --> 16:54.347
